cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.AI - The paper introduces a new set of reinforcement learning tasks in Minecraft and compares existing deep reinforcement learning architectures with new memory-based DRL architectures. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence. 
2. cs.LG - The paper evaluates the generalization performance of the architectures on environments not used during training, which is a common topic in machine learning and specifically falls under the sub-category of learning. 
3. cs.CV - The tasks involve high-dimensional visual observations, which is a common topic in computer vision. 
4. cs.RO - The paper involves controlling actions in a 3D world, which falls under the category of robotics. 
5. cs.GR - The paper involves controlling active perception in a 3D world, which falls under the category of graphics.
